# ðŸ”’ Building Scalable REST APIs with Node.js and Express

Node.js and Express power millions of APIs in 2025. Learn to create secure, scalable APIs with this in-depth guide covering everything from basic setup to advanced production optimizations.

## ðŸ—ï¸ API Design Principles

### RESTful Best Practices:
- **Resource-Based URLs**: `/api/v1/users`, `/api/v1/posts`
- **Proper HTTP Methods**: GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE
- **Standard Status Codes**: 200, 201, 400, 401, 404, 500
- **Versioning**: Always version your API (`/api/v1/`)
- **Consistent Response Format**

### Response Standard:
```javascript
{
  "success": true,
  "data": { /* resource data */ },
  "message": "Operation successful",
  "timestamp": "2024-12-28T10:30:00.000Z"
}
```

## âš¡ Core Setup & Configuration

### 1. Project Structure
```
api/
